gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

 Whoever has this worldly pleasure, knows his own suffering in darkness; 
 The body and senses are tied to the mind and soul, so they recognize their enemy's happiness.

Here is the translation:

Came I Maharaja's city Meghapure; They will not stay here today;
Know such and one who makes a mistake, Oh Har, our sin is great.

Here is the translation:

The joyful people in joyous play, and this darkness is our Diwali; 
That day went away to Bhadar's kingdom, making oneself the great king.
